This paper is about semantic web search, which involves improving the accuracy of search results by understanding the intent of the search and providing contextually relevant results. This topic is closely related to information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and databases (cs.DB), as well as social networks (cs.SI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.IR, followed by cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.SI, and cs.CL.
